ECB Drains 163 Billion Euros in Deposits to Offset Bond Program

-- B y   G a b i   T h e s i n g
-- 
2011-10-11T11:04:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/ecb-drains-163-billion-euros-in-deposits-to-offset-bond-program.html
The  European Central Bank  said it
drained 163 billion euros ($223 billion), to offset the extra
liquidity created by its government bond purchases.  The Frankfurt-based central bank said that 108 banks
submitted bids totalling 242 billion euros.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gabi Thesing at 
 gthesing@bloomberg.net  